12 (c) a narrative describing the judge’s performance with, at the option of the commission, an overall
13 score on a numerical scale from one to five;
14 (d) at the option of the judge evaluated, a written statement not to exceed 200 words submitted by
15 the judge within 15 days of receiving a copy of the report; and
16 (e) any other information the commission considers necessary to include in the report, including
17 reliably reported improprieties in the judge's conduct of the judge's office.
18 (3) The report may refer to information from a judge's earlier judicial performance report only if
19 necessary to provide context for the current reporting period.
20 (4) The commission shall make each report publicly available on the internet and may make
21 reports publicly available by other means consistent with budgetary constraints.
22 (5) The commission shall provide a summary of the preelection report for each judge running at
23 the ensuing election to the secretary of state for publication in a judicial evaluation information pamphlet as
24 provided in [section 10].
25 (6) The commission shall provide the court administrator with each report that becomes public
